ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.131                Enzyme
NAME        carotenoid 1,2-hydratase;
            CrtC
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     lycopene hydro-lyase (1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene-forming)
REACTION    (1) 1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene = lycopene + H2O [RN:R07519];
            (2) 1,1'-dihydroxy-1,1',2,2'-tetrahydrolycopene = 1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene + H2O [RN:R09790]
ALL_REAC    R07519 R09790;
            (other) R07516 R07522 R07528 R07532 R07536 R07539 R07543
SUBSTRATE   1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene [CPD:C19795];
            1,1'-dihydroxy-1,1',2,2'-tetrahydrolycopene [CPD:C19894]
PRODUCT     lycopene [CPD:C05432];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene [CPD:C19795]
COMMENT     In Rubrivivax gelatinosus [1] and Thiocapsa roseopersicina [2] both products are formed, whereas Rhodobacter capsulatus [1] only gives 1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydrolycopene. Also acts on neurosporene giving 1-hydroxy-1,2-dihydroneurosporene with both organism but 1,1'-dihydroxy-1,1',2,2'-tetrahydroneurosporene only with Rubrivivax gelatinosus.
